<reg_short_dscr>:
Policer update interval
------------------------------
<reg_public_text>:
Configure the leaky bucket update interval for the ACL, storm- and port policers. 
This configuration affects the policing rate unit for these 3 policers. 
By setting this parameter to a clock frequency dependent value, the rate unit can be kept identical/similar across different system clock frequencies.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This configuration will affect the policing rate unit for the storm, ACL and port policers. The rate unit is calculated as follows:

Rate unit = SYS_CLK / (POL_UPD_INT * 32) bps

Recommended value and corresponding rate unit:
250MHz: 312 => 25040bps
500MHz: 624 => 25040bps
625MHz: 780 => 25040bps

Frame rate mode is also affected be this setting. The default frame rate unit is 10fps (frames per second). This is scaled according to this formula:
Frame rate = 10fps * (Rate unit / 25040bps)
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0-31: Not allowed
N: Update interval
------------------------------
